---
// src/components/mdc/Partners.astro
//
// Ported from v1-final app/components/content/Partners.vue.
// The legacy component fetched the /partners content from Nuxt Content local
// markdown files and rendered it with markdown-it.
//
// In Astro the partner organization listing is static — rendered as plain HTML
// matching the content from the Strapi "partners" page body.
// This component is used when body = ":Partners" MDC syntax is detected.
---

<div class="partners-body">
  <div class="partners-indent">
    <p>
      <a href="https://icjia.illinois.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Illinois Criminal Justice Information Authority (ICJIA)</a>
      is the lead agency responsible for housing and supporting InfoNet. ICJIA staff oversee InfoNet's design and upgrades,
      provide training and technical assistance to users, use InfoNet's data for research and planning, and works with partners
      to govern InfoNet's use and growth.
    </p>
    <p>
      All four InfoNet partners below work routinely with ICJIA to govern InfoNet's use and data requirements; use InfoNet's
      data for grant monitoring, research, and strategic planning; and cohosting/facilitating forums and/or relaying feedback
      from the field about how InfoNet can be improved.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://www.ilcadv.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Illinois Coalition Against Domestic Violence (ICADV)</a>
      is a membership organization working to eliminate domestic violence in Illinois and increase access to ever-improving services
      for survivors of all backgrounds. ICADV serves over 50 domestic violence programs statewide that provide direct service to
      survivors and their dependent children.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://icasa.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Illinois Coalition Against Sexual Assault</a>
      is a unified network of over 30 rape crisis centers, envisioning a world free of sexual violence, and working together to
      end sexual violence in Illinois.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://www.dhs.state.il.us/page.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Illinois Department of Human Services' (IDHS)</a>
      Bureau of Domestic Violence, Sexual Assault, and Human Trafficking assists Illinois residents to live free from domestic violence,
      sexual assault, and human trafficking by promoting prevention and working in partnership with communities in advancing equality,
      dignity, and respect for all. IDHS administers federal and state funding to over 60 domestic violence and 30 sexual assault centers.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://www.chicago.gov/city/en/depts/fss.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Chicago Department of Family &amp; Support Services' (CDFSS)</a>
      Division on Domestic Violence leads the City of Chicago's multi-layered response to domestic violence. CDFSS supports a network
      of about 20 service providers that address victims' counseling and legal needs.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  /* Match flush-left alignment of sibling sections (InfoNet team, etc.).
     Previous version added extra padding (4rem at desktop) + 25 px
     margin-left, pushing the column right and looking double-indented. */
  .partners-body {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-body);
  }

  .partners-body p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .partners-body a {
    /* link-deep #0353a4 = 7.6:1 — 1.4.6 (AAA); input-focus #1565c0 was 5.75:1 */
    color: var(--color-link-deep);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .partners-body a:hover {
    color: var(--color-link-strong);
  }

  .partners-body a:focus {
    outline: 2px solid var(--color-primary);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }
</style>
